  "informal_statement": "For every integer-valued sequence a : ℕ -> ℤ and natural number n, the sum of consecutive differences a(i+1) - a(i) over range n telescopes to a(n) - a(0).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n: the base case n = 0 is the empty sum equalling a(0) - a(0) = 0. In the successor step, split off the last term with Finset.sum_range_succ, apply the inductive hypothesis (the sum up to n telescopes to a(n) - a(0)), and close the resulting a(n) - a(0) + (a(n+1) - a(n)) = a(n+1) - a(0) identity with ring.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem telescoping_sum (a : ℕ → ℤ) (n : ℕ) : (∑ i ∈ Finset.range n, (a (i + 1) - a i)) = a n - a 0",
