  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 10b7c24b), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Deliberately picked as a general, reusable lemma (the telescoping principle itself) rather than another specific closed-form instance -- every prior sum packet in this domain (sum_odds, sum_evens, sum_squares, sum_cubes, gauss_sum, geom_series_sum_induction) proves one particular closed form, whereas this proves the general mechanism that underlies them; a future packet could re-derive e.g. gauss_sum as a corollary via a (i) = i*(i+1)/2-style telescoping term, though that cross-reference is not attempted here.",
